-- German State Minister Opposes Transaction Tax, Handelsblatt Says
-- B y   A l l i s o n   C o n n o l l y
-- 2012-01-30T06:44:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/german-state-minister-opposes-transaction-tax-handelsblatt-says.html
German State Minister Volker Bouffier is opposed to a transaction tax because it would mean
job losses,  Handelsblatt  quoted him as saying.  A stock transfer tax is reasonable if necessary, the
newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in  Frankfurt  at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 